726966f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., at the S.E. corner of Carpenter Ave., showing in a set of two views the George Alexander House of 1891.  Other owners were A. Colyer, 1860; Mrs. Leven, 1873; J.M. Alexander, 1891; and the above mentioned Alexander.  In 1883 the house was not in its present shape.  At this time it was an orphanage probably conducted
by Mrs. Leven.

May 1923.
View 2: April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
